in a more diverse environment. To be the future leaders of a more democratic world, they must be at ease with everything from highbrow art to everyday life--from Beowulf to Jaws--and view hierarchies as ladders to scale. Through deft portrayals of the relationships among students, faculty, and staff, Khan shows how members of the new elite face the opening of society while still preserving the advantages that allow them to rule.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aBoarding schoolsxSocial aspectszNew HampshirezConcord. 0aBoarding schoolszNew HampshirezConcordxHistory. 7aEDUCATION / Secondary.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978140083622240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400836222423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781400836222/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles